<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[701,1228,210,1523]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<materialsCitation country="Australia" location="Queensland" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Queensland">
DISTRIBUTION (fig. 4): Known from three widely separated localities in 
<collectingRegion box="[1087,1223,1147,1171]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Queensland</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[701,902,1176,1200]" country="Australia" name="South Australia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">South Australia</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[997,1223,1176,1200]" country="Australia" name="Western Australia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Western Australia</collectingRegion>
. Given the wide distribution of its host plant, 
<taxonomicName box="[701,871,1235,1259]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysocephalum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="apiculatum">
<emphasis box="[701,871,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">C. apiculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species may be very widespread in 
<collectingCountry box="[868,977,1264,1288]" name="Australia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Australia</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
